      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A sudden \"pop\" in the ear followed by sudden deafness is likely a ruptured eustachian tube or a sudden inner ear issue requiring prompt medical attention to prevent permanent damage. While tinnitus involves ringing, the complete loss of hearing suggests a structural problem or neural event that is not something to manage at home. Since you are in Oslo, please contact an emergency line or go to the nearest hospital during night hours, as sudden sensorineural hearing loss is treated best with medication within 24 to 48 hours. Ignoring this could significantly reduce your chances of recovering your hearing.",
